{
  "global": "Design and validate a spectral flow cytometry immunostain panel to identify NK and ILC developmental subsets using surface receptors and lineage-specific transcription factors in peripheral blood and tonsil samples.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Define target cell populations and marker strategy based on NK/ILC developmental biology",
      "atomics": [
        "Research NK cell developmental trajectory from CD34+ progenitors through CD56bright and CD56dim stages to terminal maturation",
        "Research ILC lineage definitions (ILC1, ILC2, ILC3) and their distinctive surface phenotype signatures",
        "Identify lineage-specifying transcription factors (T-bet for ILC1/NK, GATA3 for ILC2, RORγt for ILC3)",
        "Compile comprehensive marker list: lineage markers (CD3, CD5, CD19, CD20), developmental markers (CD34, CD56, CD161), subset markers (CD117, CRTH2)",
        "Extract gating strategies from published NK/ILC spectral flow protocols to establish best-practice hierarchies"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Assess Aurora spectral cytometer detector configuration and optimize fluorophore-to-detector assignments",
      "atomics": [
        "Enumerate total detector count and spectral sensitivity ranges available on Aurora spectral cytometer",
        "Compile available conjugate options from BioLegend, BD, and Miltenyi (FITC, PE, PE-Cy5, APC, BV405, BV421, BV510, etc.)",
        "Create spectral overlap matrix for planned fluorophores and identify potential spillover conflicts",
        "Verify critical marker combinations (CD56/CD161, CD117/CRTH2, transcription factors) can be spectrally unmixed without cross-contamination",
        "Design optimal fluorophore-to-detector assignment strategy maximizing resolution of closely related populations"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Select specific antibody clones and conjugates from available sources",
      "atomics": [
        "Create antibody specification table with clone names, catalog numbers, fluorescent conjugates, and expected brightness for each target marker",
        "Cross-reference availability across BioLegend, BD, and Miltenyi catalogs for each required clone",
        "Prioritize clones based on published citations in NK/ILC flow cytometry literature and vendor recommendations",
        "Verify conjugate brightness is appropriate for Aurora spectral cytometer sensitivity, prioritizing bright conjugates for dim populations",
        "Place orders with validated lot numbers and verify receipt and storage at appropriate temperature"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Prepare cryopreserved samples and establish single-color baseline compensation parameters",
      "atomics": [
        "Thaw cryopreserved peripheral blood and tonsil samples using standard temperature-controlled protocol and verify >70% viability",
        "Prepare single-color stain controls using individual antibodies at saturating concentration on separate aliquots of cells",
        "Run single-color controls on Aurora spectral cytometer to establish PMT voltages that achieve ~3-4 log decade separation",
        "Generate single-color reference files for each fluorophore-detector combination to calculate compensation matrix",
        "Validate compensation matrix by running mixed-color positive/negative control samples"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Develop and optimize the complete multi-parameter staining panel and gating strategy",
      "atomics": [
        "Design complete staining panel combining all surface markers, transcription factors, and viability dye with optimized fluorophore assignments",
        "Perform antibody concentration titration experiments (0.01-5 µg/mL range) on positive control cells to determine optimal concentration per antibody",
        "Optimize staining protocol parameters: incubation time, temperature, washing steps, permeabilization reagents, sample volume per staining",
        "Develop complete gating hierarchy: singlets → live cells → CD3/CD5/CD19/CD20 negative → CD56 vs CD161 (separate NK from ILC) → subset identification via CD117/CRTH2/transcription factors",
        "Apply spectral unmixing to single-color controls and validate compensation across all parameter combinations"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Validate panel performance on target tissues and measure transcription factor expression in identified populations",
      "atomics": [
        "Stain fresh or thawed peripheral blood samples with optimized panel and acquire ≥50,000 live singlet events on Aurora spectral cytometer",
        "Stain tonsil samples with optimized panel and verify expected increased ILC frequency in secondary lymphoid tissue",
        "Apply developed gating strategy to identify NK cell stages (CD56bright developmental vs CD56dim mature) and ILC subsets (ILC1, ILC2, ILC3) in both tissues",
        "Measure lineage-specific transcription factor expression (T-bet, GATA3, RORγt) in each identified population via median fluorescence intensity",
        "Assess reproducibility by analyzing multiple replicates and samples from different donors and batch sources"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Maintain detailed experimental notebook documenting all PMT voltages, antibody concentrations, incubation times, compensation matrices, and gating logic",
    "Establish internal quality control standards with reference population frequencies and transcription factor expression ranges from ≥5 healthy donors",
    "Generate final validation report with annotated flow cytometry plots demonstrating spectral resolution, compensation quality, and identification of all target populations"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Optimize and validate a 15-parameter spectral flow panel on Aurora spectral cytometer to identify CD56bright/CD56dim NK cells and CD117+/CRTH2+ ILC subsets stratified by T-bet/GATA3/RORγt expression in cryopreserved peripheral blood and tonsil samples using BioLegend, BD, and Miltenyi antibodies.",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Document NK developmental stages (CD34+ progenitor, CD56bright developmental, CD56dim mature, terminal KIR+) and ILC subsets (ILC1: T-bet+RORγt-, ILC2: CRTH2+GATA3+, ILC3: RORγt+) with gating markers CD3-, CD5-, CD56, CD161, CD117, CRTH2",
        "atomics": [
          "Retrieve developmental trajectory data: NK stages progress from CD56brightCD16- (immature) through CD56dimCD16+ (mature) with inverse KIR acquisition",
          "Compile ILC phenotypes from recent literature: ILC1 (CD3-CD5-CD56-CD161+CD117-T-bet+), ILC2 (CD3-CD5-CD56-CD161+CD117+CRTH2+GATA3+), ILC3 (CD3-CD5-CD56-CD161+CD117+RORγt+)",
          "Define lineage markers for innate gating: CD3, CD5, CD19, CD20 all negative to exclude T cells, B cells, and non-lymphoid populations",
          "Identify secondary markers for ILC/NK discrimination: CD56 positive in NK (all stages), CD56 negative in ILC; CD161 positive in both lineages",
          "Extract published gating hierarchies from Serafini/Mazzurana NK/ILC spectral flow protocols and Magri ILC flow cytometry reference panels"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Map to Aurora spectral detector configuration (6L or 5L) and calculate spillover matrix for surface marker + intracellular transcription factor panel",
        "atomics": [
          "Confirm Aurora 6L detectors (FITC, PE, PE-Cy5, APC, APC-Cy7, BV405/BV421/BV510/BV650 regions) or 5L (reduced BV channels)",
          "Assign surface markers to non-overlapping regions: CD3/CD5 (FITC/PE), CD56/CD161/CD117/CRTH2 (PE-Cy5/APC/APC-Cy7/BV), viability dye (BV405)",
          "Assign intracellular transcription factors to minimally overlapping conjugates: T-bet (AF488), GATA3 (PE-Cy7), RORγt (APC or AF647)",
          "Pre-calculate spillover percentages: expect <15% spillover from bright markers (PE, APC) into adjacent detectors; <5% for transcription factors",
          "Design compensation protocol: generate matrix from single-color controls (≥10,000 events each), test unmixing on mixed positive/negative samples"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Order validated antibodies: CD3 (clone UCHT1), CD5, CD19, CD20, CD34, CD56 (clone HCD56 or NK56), CD161 (clone HP-3G10), CD117 (YB5.B8), CRTH2, T-bet, GATA3, RORγt, viability dye from BioLegend/BD/Miltenyi",
        "atomics": [
          "Select BioLegend CD3-FITC clone UCHT1, CD56-PE clone HCD56, CD161-BV421 clone HP-3G10 (BD Biosciences) for optimal spectral performance on Aurora",
          "Verify BD Biosciences offers CD34-APC (clone 8G12), CRTH2-BV510 for ILC2 discrimination; Miltenyi provides T-bet-AF488, GATA3-PE-Cy7, RORγt-APC panels",
          "Cross-check brightness values (AU) from vendor datasheets: target ≥400 AU MFI for transcription factors (typically dim in ILC1), ≥800 AU for surface markers",
          "Place consolidated order prioritizing 25 µL optimal-concentration aliquots to reduce waste; request same lot numbers for 3-month reproducibility",
          "Upon delivery, validate all conjugates with Rainbow Calibration beads (5 or 8-peak) to confirm brightness within expected range"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Thaw cryopreserved PBMC and tonsil samples; prepare single-color controls at saturating concentration; run to establish PMT gain and generate compensation references",
        "atomics": [
          "Thaw cryopreserved PBMCs at 37°C, immediately transfer to pre-warmed RPMI-10% FBS, incubate 30 min, then centrifuge 300g 5 min and wash 2x to remove cryoprotectant",
          "Assess viability with 7-AAD: expect >75% live cells; if <70%, do not proceed with staining (sample quality too poor)",
          "Thaw tonsil sample, prepare single-cell suspension via enzymatic dissociation (collagenase II 1 mg/mL, 30 min, 37°C) followed by mechanical triturating and 40 µm filtering",
          "Prepare 10-12 single-color controls: aliquot 0.5×10^6 cells per tube, stain with individual antibody at 2-5 µg/mL (saturating) or per vendor recommendation, incubate 30 min at 4°C",
          "Wash 3x with PBS-2% FBS, fix with 2% paraformaldehyde, run on Aurora and record PMT voltages that achieve singlet population >2000 on y-axis, bright/dim separated by ≥3 decades"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Combine 15 parameters into single panel; titrate each antibody (0.01-5 µg/mL range); optimize staining/permeabilization protocol; generate compensation matrix via Aurora software",
        "atomics": [
          "Design 15-parameter panel layout: Row 1 surface (CD3-FITC, CD5-PE, CD19-PerCP, CD56-PE-Cy5, CD161-BV421); Row 2 surface (CD117-BV510, CRTH2-BV650); Rows 3-4 intracellular (T-bet-AF488, GATA3-PE-Cy7, RORγt-APC, 7-AAD viability)",
          "Perform titration on PBMC samples: test each antibody at 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1.0, 5.0 µg/mL; select concentration where signal-to-noise MFI ratio ≥5:1 in positive subset with <20% spillover into adjacent detectors",
          "Optimize staining: surface stain 30 min (4°C) → wash 3x → permeabilize 15 min using Foxp3 Transcription Factor Staining Buffer Set → intracellular stain 45 min (4°C) → wash 3x → acquire",
          "Run 10 single-color compensation controls in 'Panel' mode on Aurora: acquire ≥10,000 singlet events per control at optimized PMT gains",
          "Use Aurora software (or export to FlowJo) to calculate spillover matrix: for each fluorophore, measure % signal in off-target detectors; apply Gaussian compensation model; validate by acquiring mixed 2-color positive/negative sample and confirming <5% residual spillover"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Stain peripheral blood and tonsil samples with optimized 15-parameter panel; apply gating hierarchy to identify NK stages and ILC subsets; measure transcription factor expression (MFI) per population",
        "atomics": [
          "Stain 1×10^6 PBMC per donor (n≥3) with optimized panel: surface 30 min, permeabilize, intracellular 45 min, wash, fix; acquire ≥50,000 live singlet events on Aurora at optimized voltages",
          "Apply gating sequence: singlets (FSC-A vs FSC-H gate) → live cells (7-AAD negative) → lymphocytes (FSC vs SSC) → CD3-CD5-CD19-CD20 negative (innate compartment) → CD56+ (NK) or CD56- (ILC) → further subset by CD161, CD117, CRTH2",
          "Gate NK into CD56bright (developmental marker, typically low CD16/KIR) vs CD56dim (mature, high CD16/KIR if measured) using bivariate plot CD56 vs CD16 or side-scatter",
          "Gate ILC using Boolean: ILC1 = CD117-CD161+T-bet+RORγt-; ILC2 = CD117+CRTH2+GATA3+; ILC3 = CD117+RORγt+; Calculate % of lymphocytes for each population and median T-bet/GATA3/RORγt MFI",
          "Repeat staining on tonsil samples and verify expected ≥3-5 fold higher ILC2+ILC3 frequency (secondary lymphoid tissue phenotype) and overlapping transcription factor expression ranges with PBMC"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Record in electronic lab notebook: PMT gains per detector, all antibody concentrations used (µg/mL), lot numbers, staining incubation times/temperatures, compensation matrix coefficients, complete gating hierarchy with FSC/SSC coordinates",
      "Calculate reference ranges from ≥5 healthy donors: NK% of lymphocytes (5-15%), CD56bright% of NK (10-30%), ILC% of lymphocytes (<0.5-2%), ILC1:ILC2:ILC3 ratio in PB (~1:0.1:0.5) vs tonsil (~0.5:1.5:1.5), and median MFI ranges for T-bet (1000-5000 AU in T-bet+ cells), GATA3 (2000-8000 AU), RORγt (1500-6000 AU)",
      "Prepare final validation report with 6-8 representative plots: (1) FSC/SSC singlet gate with gating percentages; (2) 7-AAD live gate; (3) CD56 vs CD161 plot showing NK (bright) vs ILC (dim/negative) separation; (4) NK CD56bright/dim bivariate split; (5) ILC subset gates on CD117 vs CRTH2 and CD117 vs RORγt; (6) T-bet/GATA3/RORγt overlay histograms by ILC subset; (7) compensation matrix showing <5% spillover residuals; (8) side-by-side PBMC vs tonsil frequency plots confirming expected tissue distribution"
    ]
  }
}
```
